headline: Goldman Sachs, Morgan Stanley To Lead Amazon-Backed Beta Technologies $300M GE Deal And IPO As Military-Trained Electric Aircraft Firm Expands
summary: Beta Technologies, an electric aircraft manufacturer backed by Amazon (NASDAQ:AMZN), on Monday filed for an initial public offering in the U.S. at a moment when Wall Street’s appetite for growth stories has rarely been stronger. The filing arrives during what analysts describe as one of the most favorable periods for public listings in years, according to Reuters.
